The paper discusses sampling-based motion planners, which are commonly used in robotics and control systems, indicating a likely fit for the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses Monte Carlo experiments and probabilistic guarantees, suggesting a potential fit for the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
